# Blueprint Architectural Memory Rule

Before creating any new helper, utility, service, component, API route, or abstraction, call Blueprint MCP tools.

Use:
- `find_existing_abstractions`
- `suggest_file_placement`
- `suggest_import_reuse`

Do not say you will create a new helper until Blueprint has confirmed no reusable abstraction exists.

Workflow:
1. Call `find_existing_abstractions` first.
2. If HIGH or MEDIUM confidence match exists, reuse or extend the existing abstraction.
3. Only create a new helper if Blueprint returns no meaningful match.
4. Never create a parallel utility when an existing utility can be safely extended.

If Blueprint returns high-confidence reuse, prefer importing the existing abstraction instead of creating duplicate code.
If Blueprint returns placement guidance, follow the suggested path.
